-- pg_turbovec v1.22.0 -- repo cleanup: remove the deprecated
-- turbovec.mmap_static_blocked no-op GUC; drift-check/formatting
-- fixes; no functional changes.
--
-- This file is a *reference mirror*. The authoritative install
-- script is generated by `cargo pgrx schema`.
--
-- v1.22.0 removes `turbovec.mmap_static_blocked`, which had been a
-- deprecated no-op since v1.19.0 (when pg_turbovec's relfile mmap
-- fast path -- the thing this GUC toggled -- was deleted). Per the
-- documented deprecation policy in AGENTS.md (a removed GUC needs a
-- minor bump, not a patch, and at least one prior minor's warning
-- window), this is the removal half of a "warn for a minor, then
-- remove" pair that started at v1.19.0 and has now spanned three
-- minors (v1.19.0 warn, v1.20.0/v1.21.0 still-warning, v1.22.0
-- remove). `SET turbovec.mmap_static_blocked = ...` now errors like
-- any other unknown GUC instead of silently no-op'ing.
--
-- No wire-format change (MetaPageData::version stays 5). No other
-- SQL surface change. No REINDEX. `ALTER EXTENSION pg_turbovec
-- UPDATE TO '1.22.0';` is sufficient.
--
-- (intentionally empty beyond this note -- there is no DDL to run;
-- removing a GUC is a Rust-side registration change, not a SQL
-- object.)
